D. Robert "Bob" Graham Papers
DESCRIPTION CONTAINER LIST DIGITAL OBJECTS SEARCH
Container List
Correspondence and Subject Files, 1959-1984
This series is comprised of correspondence, reports, notes, background material, memoranda, and meeting minutes. Although most files contain correspondence, some are subject files that include publications, reports and similar material on a certain topic or topics. Prominent topics include education, environmental conservation, Florida politics and economics, and health care. Other topics include the Equal Rights Amendment, the Cross Florida Barge Canal, aging, Dade County issues, desegregation, the Education Commission of the States, Lands for You, abortion, Interama, 4 Clean Water, the Select Council on Post-High School Education (SCOPE), underground power, the YMCA, and land use. Files are arranged alphabetically.
( click here to show the contents of this series )
Legislative Files, 1967-1978
This series consists primarily of materials pertaining to Graham-sponsored legislation, including copies of bills, correspondence, and reports. In addition, the series includes some material on general legislation not sponsored by Graham, as well as correspondence related to this legislation. A small amount of federal and non-Florida legislation is also included. Although most of the files deal with specific pieces of legislation or legislative issues, there are also several files containing legislative summaries of bills introduced by Graham during specific sessions. A small portion of the material pertains to the activities and organization of the Florida legislature. Files are arranged alphabetically, and many folders also contain bill numbers (e.g., SB 56) in the folder title.

Committee Files, 1963-1976
Correspondence, meeting minutes, reports, notes, memoranda, press releases, and materials related to committee hearings. Most of the committees are either Senate or House of Representatives, but there are a small number of joint or special committees. Most of the files pertain to education, particularly those from the Senate Committee on Education, the Interim Committee on Higher Education, and the other education-related committees. In addition, there is a great deal of overlap between the various House committees from 1966 to 1970 pertaining to education: Appropriations, Higher Education, Public Schools. Files are arranged alphabetically.
( click here to show the contents of this series )
Speeches, 1962-1984
This series is comprised of speeches and the outlines of speeches made by Graham. In addition to the speech outlines, statements, and addresses, the majority of the files also contain correspondence, notes, and background material pertaining to the speeches. Files are arranged alphabetically.
( click here to show the contents of this series )
News Clippings, 1966-1976
Trip Files, 1966-1976
This series includes material related to official and personal trips. The majority of the files represent meetings attended by Graham, including meetings of the Education Commission of the States, the League of Women Voters, Southern Regional Education Board, and congressional meetings in various Florida cities. Files are arranged alphabetically.
( click here to show the contents of this series )
Itineraries, 1977-1978
This series consists primarily of itineraries and schedules from 1977 and 1978, during the gubernatorial election. In addition to Graham's itineraries, the files also include those of his running mate, Wayne Mixson. In addition to campaign activities and venues, the itineraries represent official activities during this period. Files are arranged chronologically.
( click here to show the contents of this series )
Office Files, 1968-1977
This small series includes files of memoranda and other documents created or received by Graham's staff members. In addition, it includes material related to staffing and the organization of the Florida Senate. Files are arranged alphabetically.
( click here to show the contents of this series )
Writings, 1966-1983
This series primarily consists of articles written by Graham for journals, newspapers, and newsletters. In addition to these published articles, the files contain drafts, notes, and correspondence pertaining to the articles. The monograph Workdays: Finding Florida on the Job is included, along with a draft version and reviews.
